<title>USA: Tesoro holder drops stake, director resigns.</title>
<headline>Tesoro holder drops stake, director resigns.</headline>
<dateline>SAN ANTONIO, Texas 1996-10-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Tesoro Petroleum Corp said Friday that Sanford Prater, a partner with Ardsley Advisory Partners, has resigned from Tesoro's board of directors, following a decline in the number of shares in the company that Ardsley holds.</p>
<p>Tesoro said that Prater had an agreement with certain shareholders that if Ardsley's holdings of Tesoro stock declined by more than 50 percent, Prater would be obligated to resign from the board.</p>
<p>Information about the number of shares held by Ardsley was not immediately available.</p>
